[
    "Operational risk refers to risks arising from inadequate or failed internal processes, people, systems, or external events.",
    "Operational risk can lead to losses in financial capital, reputation, competitive position, business opportunities, and other intangible assets.",
    "Operational risk encompasses Compliance risk, Conduct risk, Legal risk, and Estimations and Model risk.",
    "The Firm manages operational risk through its Compliance, Conduct, and Operational Risk (CCOR) Management Framework.",
    "The CCOR Management Framework is designed to enable the Firm to govern, identify, measure, monitor, test, manage, and report on operational risks.",
    "The CCOR Management Framework is executed by the Control Management Organization.",
    "The Control Management Organization consists of control managers within each Line of Business (LOB) and Corporate.",
    "The Firm's Global Chief Compliance Officer (CCO) and the Functional Risk Executive (FRE) for Operational Risk and Qualitative Risk Appetite define the CCOR Management Framework.",
    "The CCO and FRE set minimum standards for execution of the CCOR Management Framework.",
    "Each LOB and Corporate is accountable for identifying and managing operational risk.",
    "The Firm particularly focuses on Conduct risk.",
    "Conduct risk is the risk that any action or misconduct by an employee could lead to unfair outcomes.",
    "Conduct risk can impact market integrity.",
    "Conduct risk can harm employees or the Firm.",
    "Conduct risk can compromise the Firm's reputation.",
    "The Firm mitigates operational risk through insurance purchased from commercial insurers and Park Assurance Company.",
    "Park Assurance Company is a wholly-owned captive insurer.",
    "Consistent operational risk reporting is produced on a Firmwide basis and by individual LOBs and Corporate.",
    "The reporting evaluates key risk indicators against established thresholds.",
    "The reporting assesses different types of operational risks according to the Firm's risk appetite.",
    "Standards are in place for escalating these reports to senior management and the Board of Directors when necessary."
] 

